post_text: Have a safe and healthy summer!
text: Have a safe and healthy summer!

post_text:
Character Trait: TRRFCC Student

Throughout the school year, students learn about the Six Pillars of Character. This month, we’re reviewing all six character traits: Trustworthiness, Respect, Responsibility, Fairness, Caring, and Citizenship. Over the summer, we’re asking parents to discuss the importance of these character traits with their student. We also ask that parents help children make ethical decisions and encourage them to always remember the Six Pillars of Character when dealing with others. For more information, go to CharacterCounts.org.
text:
Character Trait: TRRFCC Student

Throughout the school year, students learn about the Six Pillars of Character. This month, we’re reviewing all six character traits: Trustworthiness, Respect, Responsibility, Fairness, Caring, and Citizenship. Over the summer, we’re asking parents to discuss the importance of these character traits with their student. We also ask that parents help children make ethical decisions and encourage them to always remember the Six Pillars of Character when dealing with others. For more information, go to CharacterCounts.org.

post_text:
Reminder that tomorrow is the last day to turn in ALL work from the quarter. All work is due at the school by 10:30. Vans will still do their routes if you prefer to give the work to the vans on their normal route.

Next week, no work packets will be given, and van routes will not be done. If you would like lunches, you need to pick up from the school from 7:30-9:30 Monday and Tuesday.

Tuesday is our last day of the 2019-2020 school year.

If you're child has been invited to summer school, please turn the permission form in by tomorrow.

If you would like a copy of our DVD yearbook, please contact the front office. They are $7. This year they also include videos from each class and the principal’s end of the year awards.

We look forward to returning in August! Don't forget to get in your enrollment (you can find the reenrollment on our website: http://www.heswilliams.org).

We love and miss you all and hope you have a wonderful summer.

Just a reminder for next week:

We will have breakfast/lunch bags available to pick up every day from 7:30-10:30. Please pick up on the picnic tables near the playground and give a wave to the employee in the window so we can mark down lunch counts.

Activity packets will be outside along the back building ramp. They will be organized by grade level. We will also have pencils and other supplies for those families who need those for home activities in the bins. Please come pick up a packet next week (available Monday at 7:30) for your students.

As always, for safety, please do not come pick up items if someone is currently in that area. Let's be patient, kind, and safe for the benefit of our community.

post_text:
There seems to be some confusion about our head lice policy, so I wanted to include a brief summary of the policy here:

Head Lice Policy
Students found with live head lice/or nits (eggs) may remain in class but are discouraged from close head to head contact with others. The school will communicate with the parents and discuss treatment. The school will evaluate each case on an individual basis and discuss options. The school will screen symptomatic students and in special cases may screen entire classes if high numbers of reported cases are present. Letters/notification to entire classes will not be sent home by the teacher or school, unless the teacher and administrators determine that it is needed, usually at 10% of students infested.

If you would like a copy of the whole policy, please call and we will send it home. Thank you, Mrs. Dannenberger
